<paragraph id="8B855F61FFA3FFA3FFB2D0853581739D" blockId="3.[125,203,975,999]" box="[125,203,975,999]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis id="B94E8373FFA3FFA3FFB2D0853581739D" box="[125,203,975,999]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Female</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B855F61FFA3FFA3FFB2D0B53784748D" blockId="3.[125,1173,1023,1685]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Body (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FF00D0B5340F746D" box="[207,325,1023,1047]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1A</figureCitation>
) 5.82 long, excluding setae on caudal ramus. Cephalothoracic shield subcircular, 2.12 long and 2.02 wide, excluding lateral, hyaline membrane. Fourth pediger distinctly wider than long, 0.22X0.54. Genital complex, 1.86X1.18, bottle-shaped, with posterolateral corners slightly protruded posteriorly. Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FC58D7153147740D" box="[919,1037,1119,1143]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1A</figureCitation>
) with two unequal segments, proximal segment longer than wide 1.66X0.42, and anal segment wider than long but measuring only 146X 
<quantity id="4CC2F284FFA3FFA3FD8DD7D537D774CD" box="[578,669,1181,1207]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4799999999999995" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" unit="mm" value="348.0">348 mm</quantity>
. Caudal ramus (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FCA1D7D536A774CD" box="[878,1005,1183,1207]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[125,185,1338,1357]" captionTargetBox="[253,1041,138,1278]" captionTargetId="figure-98@5.[250,1048,133,1303]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Leg 1, with tip shown in ventral view (upper insertion) and dorsal view (lower insertion); (B) leg 2; (C) leg 3; (D) leg 4; (E) left half of anal somite and caudal ramus, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582145" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582145/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 2E</figureCitation>
) attaching to posterolateral surface of anal segment, distinctly wider than long, 28X 
<quantity id="4CC2F284FFA3FFA3FC78D7F5314874AD" box="[951,1026,1213,1239]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" unit="mm" value="64.0">64 mm</quantity>
; armed with three short and three long setae. Egg sac not seen.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B855F61FFA3FFA4FF57D7B4368D75F8" blockId="3.[125,1173,1023,1685]" lastBlockId="4.[138,1185,1321,1476]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="403" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Antennule (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FED1D7B434D8756C" box="[286,402,1278,1302]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1B</figureCitation>
) two-segmented; proximal segment carrying on anterodistal surface 25 setose and two naked setae (on dorsal side), distal segment short, about 2.42 times as long as wide, with one subterminal seta on posterior margin and 11 setae plus two aesthetascs on distal margin. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FE50D614375F750C" box="[415,533,1374,1398]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1C</figureCitation>
, with broken tip) three-segmented; proximal segment smallest, with spatula-like process on posteromedial corner; second segment subrectangular and unarmed; distal segment long, curved claw bearing two setae, one proximal and other one close to medial region. Postantennal process lacking, except two usual, setule-bearing papillae. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FF34D694343B758C" box="[251,369,1502,1526]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1D</figureCitation>
) with four sections; bearing 12 teeth on medial margin of distal blade. Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FF35D6B73424766F" box="[250,366,1533,1557]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1C</figureCitation>
) comprising stout dentiform process and basal papilla with two short and one long setae. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FE3CD557372F764F" box="[499,613,1565,1589]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1E</figureCitation>
) two-segmented; proximal segment (lacertus) unarmed; slender distal segment (brachium) carrying subterminal, hyaline membrane on outer edge, terminal calamus slightly longer than subterminal canna. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA3FFA3FBD6D51731C0760F" box="[1049,1162,1629,1653]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figure 1F</figureCitation>
) three-segmented; proximal segment (corpus) unarmed, twice as long as next two segments combined (subchela); middle (shaft) segment armed distally with a pinnate seta and in middle region small, blunt element; distal (claw) segment sharply pointed and slightly bent. Box of sternal furca (
<figureCitation id="130143E4FFA4FFA4FEE9D62034D675F8" box="[294,412,1386,1410]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" captionTargetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" captionTargetId="figure-56@4.[262,1060,133,1208]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Caligus arii Bassett-Smith, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Figure 1G</figureCitation>
) subsquare, carrying two tines with truncate tip.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF450FE9FFA4FFA4FF45D79636D57570" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4582141" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4582141" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4582141/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" startId="4.[138,198,1244,1263]" targetBox="[262,1058,133,1205]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B855F61FFA4FFA4FF45D79636D57570" blockId="4.[138,1185,1244,1290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
Figure 1. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A24E2FFA4FFA4FF26D79634927495" authority="Bassett-Smith" authorityName="Bassett-Smith" authorityYear="1898" box="[233,472,1244,1263]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Caligidae" genus="Caligus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siphonostomatoida" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arii">
<emphasis id="B94E8373FFA4FFA4FF26D79634047495" box="[233,334,1244,1263]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Caligus arii</emphasis>
Bassett-Smith
</taxonomicName>
, adult female. (A) Habitus, dorsal; (B) antennule; (C) antenna, postantennal process, and maxillule; (D) mandible; (E) maxilla; (F) maxilliped; (G) sternal furca.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B855F61FFA4FFA4FF6AD6C1341B75BE" blockId="4.[138,1185,1321,1476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Armature on rami of legs 1–4 as follows (Roman numerals indicating spines and Arabic numerals, setae):</paragraph>
